## README file for VM snapshot management using Ansible. 
## The playbook can help orchestrate VM creation/deletion tasks pre/post patching activity


## FILES ##
# vm_snapshot_inventory --> inventory file
# vm_snapshot.yml       --> playbook to run
# vars.yml              --> variable file

## Inventory file ##
# Add the server names in sections based on the vcenter 

## Vars file ##
# Update the username and password variable
# Update the patching change number
# Update the action (create, remove or view snapshot)

# Sample vars:
# vcenter_username: ent\pa_shoms5
# vcenter_password: \x4tf~W/@-xkUpuB
# change_number: CHG000001
# snapshot_action: remove

## command to execute ##

# ansible-playbook vm_snapshot.yml -i vm_snapshot_inventory --limit <hostgroup>

# where hostgroup is one of HOU1|HOU2|HOU2-ORACLE-WLC|MGP1|POS1|SHE1|YXE
